  "timeframe": "5m",
  "market_context": "ES on the 5-minute was trending down with bearish order flow. Price failed to close below a prior low, signalling potential exhaustion of the downside delivery before a structural shift higher.",
  "key_observation": "After the market structure shift, an order block and fair value gap formed. Price respected the FVG's consequent encroachment and the order block, then engineered a sweep of a low (inducement) before expanding higher to take buy-side liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the prevailing bearish order flow on the 5-minute ES chart with price trending down.",
    "Step 2: Note the failure to close below the prior low, signalling weakness in bearish delivery.",
    "Step 3: Observe price breaking the intermediate high, confirming a market structure shift upward.",
    "Step 4: Mark the resulting bullish PD arrays — the order block and fair value gap left behind by the displacement.",
    "Step 5: Wait for price to retrace into the fair value gap (respecting its consequent encroachment) and the order block.",
    "Step 6: Identify the engineered sell-side liquidity below a short-term low as the inducement target.",
    "Step 7: Anticipate entry on the sweep of that low while price holds the PD array, with stop beyond the inducement low and partials at the prior high.",
    "Step 8: Expect expansion higher toward buy-side liquidity above the previous high."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "After a market structure shift, expect price to engineer an inducement sweep into a PD array (order block / FVG) before the true expansion. Entering on the inducement sweep within the PD array provides a tight stop and high R:R toward the prior high.",
